{
  "texts": [
    "These percentages should not be overinterpreted as they only indicate that an outcome was present in a study, but not how strong or consistent it was.",
    "For instance, if a study reported overall benefits of saliency maps but costs in a single condition, it would still contribute to the category of benefits and costs equally.",
    "Therefore, a quantitative integration of the results is not particularly informative and the effects will be investigated more thoroughly in the following sections.",
    "Before delving into the factors that modulated the effects of saliency maps, it may be informative to gain an overview of the reported biases.",
    "First, when saliency maps highlight informative areas, people tend to infer that the AI is correct (Ray et al., 2021)."
  ]
}